CAPE TOWN – Virat Kohli struck a majestic 160 not out as India thrashed South Africa by 124 runs in Wednesday's third one-day international at Newlands to take a 3-0 lead in the six-match series. #SAvIND - RESULT:
		India comprehensively defeat the Proteas by 124 runs to take a 3-0 lead in the 6-match ODI series. pic.twitter.com/TvAsyI5FzS India made 303 for 6 after being sent in to bat, while Kuldeep Yadav and Yuzvendra Chahal took four wickets apiece as South Africa were bowled out for just 179. READ: Proteas remain positive as they look to shift the ODI momentum Scores in brief: India 303-6 in 50 overs (S. Dhawan 76, V. Kohli 160 not out) South Africa 179 in 40 overs (J. Duminy 51; Y. Chahal 4-46, Kuldeep Yadav 4-23). Result: India won by 124 runs Series: India lead the six-match series 3-0 Toss: South Africa AFP